   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter" part="N" org="uniform" sample="complete">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1842-09_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute/>
            </opener>
            <p part="N">
               <note anchored="true">62</note>
               <note anchored="true">1842</note>
               <lb/>
               know then that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeL1" instant="false" full="yes">Lucy</persName>and<persName ref="./personography.xml#EdgeF3" instant="false" full="yes">Fanny</persName>
               <lb/>
               <persName ref="./personography.xml#EdgeF3" instant="false" full="yes">(M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>Wilson)</persName> are now both well<lb/>
               and they and <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM2" instant="false" full="yes">Packenham</persName>
               <lb/>
               and the Butlers &amp; the Fox<lb/>
               children all having been<lb/>
               with us round <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               This summer have made<lb/>
               it a memorable summer<lb/>
               for happiness to which we shall<lb/>
               look back with pleasure all<lb/>
               the rest of our lives<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               <quote>You may break, you may injure<lb/>
                  the vase as you will<lb/>
                  But the smell of the roses will stick<lb/>
                  to it still</quote>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" instant="false" full="yes">M<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>Edgeworth</persName> has perfectly<lb/>
               recovered her health this year<lb/>
               after the severe rheumatic<lb/>
               fever she had last year - She is<lb/>
               now not only as strong and<lb/>
               active as ever but almost with<lb/>
               as fresh a bloom in her cheeks<lb/>
               which seems like the expression<lb/>
               of mind that never fades-<lb/>
               Her silver grey hairs both contrast<lb/>
               <note anchored="true">? Sept 1842.</note>
            </p>
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Bodleian_702_1842-09_page02.jpg"/>
            <p part="N">
               <note anchored="true">1842</note>
               <lb/>
               and suit her whole <choice>
                  <orig>appear<lb/>
                  -ance</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">appearance</reg>
               </choice> - 
               <choice>
                  <orig>shewing</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">showing</reg>
               </choice>
               <del instant="false" status="unremarkable">how to be</del>
               <lb/>
               without admixture or <choice>
                  <orig>adop-<lb/>
                  tion</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">adoption</reg>
               </choice> of fake hair that she<lb/>
               has no desire to <hi rend="underline">appear</hi>young<lb/>
               but that the real freshness<lb/>
               of youth is preserved in her<lb/>
               by nature -<lb/>
            </p>
            <p part="N">So much for boasting of<lb/>
               one's own family - please<lb/>
               to burn - &amp; consider it as<lb/>
               not my own <persName ref="./Personography.xml/#EdgeA2" instant="false" full="yes">mother</persName> I am<lb/>
               boasting of but my<persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2" instant="false" full="yes">
                  <choice>
                     <orig>stepmo-<lb/>
                  ther</orig>
                     <reg instant="false">stepmother</reg>
                  </choice>
               </persName> - &amp; 
               my <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1" instant="false" full="yes"/>
               <choice>
                  <orig>fathers</orig>
                  <reg instant="false">father's</reg>
               </choice> widow<lb/>
               after 25 years widowhood &amp;<lb/>
               after our having lived together<lb/>
               upwards of 44 years -<lb/>
               a good spice of truth must have<lb/>
               been in that friendship to<lb/>
               make it keep so long - &amp; not<lb/>
               a bit stale now - &amp; if <hi rend="underline">iced</hi>
               <lb/>
               only with sugar -<lb/>
            </p>
         </div>
